3ESometimes%20the%20solution%20looked%20like%20not%20eating.%20Other%20times%2C%20it%20looked%20like%20eating%20everything%20in%20sight%20and%20then%20drowning%20in%20shame.%20At%20different%20points%2C%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20anorexia%2C%20binge%20eating%20disorder%2C%20and%20the%20frustratingly%20vague%20EDNOS%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhad-every-eating-disorder-what-not-to-ask-people-struggling-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeating%20disorder%20not%20otherwise%20specified%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20labels%20shifted%2C%20but%20the%20war%20remained%20the%20same%3A%20I%20was%20at%20odds%20with%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeading%20to%20college%20ignited%20something.%20A%20new%20environment%2C%20new%20anxieties%2C%20and%20old%20beliefs%20collided%2C%20and%20suddenly%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiet-culture-cycle-nutritionist-mindset-shift-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediet%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20I'd%20grown%20up%20with%20felt%20less%20like%20background%20noise%20and%20more%20like%20a%20tidal%20wave.%20I%20restricted.%20I%20binged.%20I%20obsessed.%20My%20body%20became%20the%20battleground%20where%20I%20tried%20to%20prove%20I%20was%20worthy%20%E2%80%94%20of%20love%2C%20success%2C%20belonging.%20It%20was%20exhausting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223eaba628-e32d-430b-aedb-96819597ad22%5C%22%3EI%20was%20nervous%20about%20what%20pregnancy%20would%20mean%20for%20my%20recovery%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecovery%20didn't%20happen%20all%20at%20once.%20It%20never%20does.%20It%20was%20slow%2C%20nonlinear%2C%20and%20full%20of%20stumbles.%20I%20relapsed.%20I%20healed.%20I%20learned%20to%20feed%20myself%20with%20food%2C%20yes%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20with%20kindness%2C%20community%2C%20and%20the%20radical%20act%20of%20rest.%20I%20learned%20that%20hunger%20wasn't%20something%20to%20be%20feared.%20It%20was%20a%20signal.%20A%20message.%20A%20chance%20to%20listen%20instead