n%20a%20Bain%20podcast%2C%20De%20Vusser%20said%20the%20firm's%20clients%20are%20grappling%20with%20massive%20amounts%20of%20change%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eincluding%20around%20artificial%20intelligence.%20It's%20a%20technology%2C%20he%20said%2C%20that's%20still%20in%20its%20early%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20continue%20to%20mature%20at%20immense%20speeds%2C%20we%20believe%2C%20in%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20on%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Vusser%20has%20also%20written%20about%20AI.%20In%20a%20recent%20LinkedIn%20post%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20Bain%20research%20that%20found%20fewer%20than%2020%25%20of%20companies%20had%20%26quot%3Bmeaningfully%20scaled%26quot%3B%20generative%20AI.%20The%20reason%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20many%20organizations%20tend%20to%20view%20AI%20%26quot%3Bprimarily%20as%20a%20technology%20initiative%20rather%20than%20using%20it%20as%20a%20catalyst%20to%20fundamentally%20reimagine%20their%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20organizations%20to%20get%20it%20right%2C%20De%20Vusser%20wrote%2C%20they%20need%20to%20simplify%20key%20processes%2C%20use%20technology%20so%20that%20it%20fits%20with%20strategic%20goals%2C%20and%20enable%20workers%20to%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b15aa2ea-53ee-448a-a4d1-bcc9b21cfe50%5C%22%3EBoston%20Consulting%20Group%20%E2%80%94%20Christoph%20Schweizer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22529%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Christoph%20Schweizer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68718ea185e81483682de8cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22397%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBCG's%20chief%20executive%2C%20Christoph%20Schweizer%2C%20starts%20his%20second%20term%20at%20the%20company%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-mistake-companies-make-bcg-tech-executive-2025-