%2C%20he%20could%20talk%20himself%20out%20of%20almost%20any%20business%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20taking%20a%20pretty%20good%20plan%20and%20just%20running%20like%20hell%2C%26quot%3B%20Samat%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20sometimes%20the%20naiveness%20of%20someone%20who%20doesn't%20have%20that%20background%20makes%20a%20much%20better%20entrepreneur.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamat%20said%20the%20decision%20to%20%26quot%3Bdo%20your%20own%20thing%26quot%3B%20and%20follow%20what%20excites%20you%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20most%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Samat%20received%20his%20second%20job%20offer%20from%20Google%20in%202008%2C%20he%20was%20initially%20hesitant%2C%20as%20he%20was%20weighing%20the%20idea%20of%20starting%20another%20company%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20was%20Marissa%20Mayer%2C%20one%20of%20Google's%20first%20engineers%2C%20who%20finally%20persuaded%20him%2C%20suggesting%20Google%20could%20be%20the%20place%20where%20he%20met%20his%20next%20cofounder.%20Others%20he%20interviewed%20with%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsundar-pichai-google-alphabet-ceo-career-life%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20%3Cspan%3EVP%20of%20product%20management%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%26quot%3Bwere%20all%20wickedly%20smart%2C%26quot%3B%20Samat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20thought%2C%20I%20bet%20I%20can%20learn%20a%20lot%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Samat%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20chase%20for%20Samat%20didn't%20quite%20end%20there.%20After%20joining%20in%202008%2C%20he%20left%20Google%20in%202015.%20When%20Pichai%20became%20CEO%2C%20he%20called%20Samat%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20come%20back.%20Samat%20said%20he%20was%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bwork%20big%20brother%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20someone%20he%20went%20to%20for%20product%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20he%20asked%20if%20I%20would%20come%20back%20to%20work%20with%20him%20on%20