%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Schweber%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68713003f748d8c055f574e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222604%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202019%2C%20Dan%20Schweber%20was%20grinding%20through%20yet%20another%20career%20pivot.%20Straight%20out%20of%20college%2C%20he%20landed%20what%20he%20thought%20would%20be%20a%20dream%20job%20as%20a%20healthcare%20consultant%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20he%20couldn't%20stand%20being%20a%20nobody%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareerist-corporate-ladder-decline-promotions-work-ethic-american-dream-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiant%20bureaucracy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20he%20joined%20a%20tiny%20healthtech%20startup%2C%20until%20it%20was%20acquired%20by%20a%20series%20of%20bigger%20companies%20that%20eventually%20laid%20him%20off.%20He%20came%20to%20believe%20that%20a%20better%20path%20would%20be%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustles-self-employment-entrepreneurship-boom-jobs-pandemic-online-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20his%20own%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he%20could%20call%20all%20the%20shots.%20So%20at%20age%2028%2C%20he%20enrolled%20in%20Columbia's%20executive%20MBA%20program.%20In%20between%20his%20day%20job%20in%20healthtech%20and%20his%20weekend%20classes%2C%20he%20used%20every%20free%20moment%20he%20could%20find%20to%20rack%20his%20brain%20for%20startup%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20in%2C%20Schweber%20had%20narrowed%20down%20his%20list%20to%20one%20promising%20contender%3A%20an%20app%20for%20physical%20therapy%20exercises.%20He%20was%20being%20treated%20for%20a%20back%20injury%20and%2C%20as%20if%20it%20were%20still%201995%2C%20his%20PT%20was%20giving%20him%20printouts%20of%20exercises%20to%20do%20at%20home.%20There%20should%20be%20an%20app%20for%20this%2C%20he%20thought.%20But%20the%20more%20he%20considered%20the%20logistics%2C%20the%20more%20doubts%20he%20had.%20Who%20would%20write%20the%20code%3F%20How%20would%20he%20find%20customers%3F%20With%20his%20student%20loans%20hanging%20over%20him%2C%20could%20he%20afford%20to%20forgo%20an%20income%20while%20he%20got%20the%20app%20off%20the%20ground%3F%20It%20all%20seemed%20so%20daunting%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20manifesting%20a%20viable%20business%20out%20of%20literally%20nothing%20in%20a%20process%20that%20was%20statistically%20doomed%20for%20failure.%20Then%20he%20saw%20a%20weeklong%20intensive%20elective%20in%20Columbia's%20course%20catalog%20that%20sounded%20kind%20of%20interesting%3A%20an%20introduction%20to%20an%20unusual%20way%20into%20small%20business%20entrepreneurship%20known%20as%20search%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20or%20more%20formally%2C%20entrepreneurship%20through%20acquisition.%20He%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20love%20at%20first%20case%20study.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20his%20first%20day%20of%20class%2C%20he%20knew%20he'd%20found%20the%20path%20he'd%20been%20looking%20for.%20%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20believe%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20%3Cem%3EI%20can%20do%20this.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20at%2036%2C%20Schweber%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%2060-plus-person%20company%2C%20calling%20all%20the%20shots%20as%20he%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20core%20idea%20behind%20search%20funds%20is%20that%2C%20in%20order%20to%20become%20an%20owner-CEO%2C%20young%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20start%20their%20own%20business%20from%20scratch.%20Instead%2C%20they%20can%20buy%20a%20business%20that%20already%20exists%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20comes%20preloaded%20with%20loyal%20customers%2C%20steady%20revenue%2C%20and%20a%20healthy%20profit%20margin.%20America%20happens%20to%20be%20chock-full%20of%20these%20businesses%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20owned%20by%20aging%20boomers%20preparing%20to%20retire.%20The%20caveat%20is%20that%20most%20of%20them%20are%20hidden%20in%20the%20unglamorous%2C%20overlooked%20corners%20of%20the%20economy.%20The%20duller%20the%20better%3A%20think%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F22-year-old-bought-car-wash-passive-income-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecar%20washes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20plumbing%2C%20snowplowing%2C%20pool%20construction%2C%20dumpster%20rentals%2C%20grease%20trap%20maintenance%20%E2%80%94%20or%20in%20Schweber's%20case%2C%20air%20duct%20cleaning.%20All%20you%20need%20is%20to%20raise%20an%20initial%20round%20of%20funding%20from%20investors%20so%20you%20can%20search%20for%20your%20business.%20Then%2C%20once%20you%20find%20the%20perfect%20business%2C%20you%20raise%20a%20bigger%20round%20to%20acquire%20it%20and%20install%20yourself%20as%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222783%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Schweber%20and%20Gary%20Codell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687130cbf748d8c055f5751d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20never%20work%20in%20a%20corporate%20job%20ever%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Schweber%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20you%20could%20give%20me.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20heard%20about%20search%20funds%20last%20fall%2C%20from%20a%20friend%20who%20was%20giving%20it%20a%20go%20after%20quitting%20her%20prestigious%20job%20in%20venture%20capital.%20A%20few%20weeks%20later%2C%20a%20management%20consultant%20I%20met%20was%20telling%20me%20about%20his%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20reunion%2C%20where%20so%20many%20people%20he%20ran%20into%20were%20starting%20a%20search%20fund%20that%20it%20became%20an%20inside%20joke%20among%20his%20former%20classmates.%20He%20kept%20trying%20to%20explain%20to%20me%20the%20mechanics%2C%20but%20everything%20about%20it%20was%20bizarre%3A%20that%20MBAs%20with%20pristine%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20would%20ditch%20their%20fancy%20corporate%20jobs%20to%20devote%20their%20lives%20to%20septic%20tanks%3B%20that%2020-%20and%2030-somethings%20would%20suddenly%20become%20the%20CEOs%20of%20multimillion-dollar%20businesses%3B%20that%20investors%20would%20give%20real%20money%20to%20people%20who%20have%20zero%20company-running%20experience%20to%20go%20run%20a%20company%20in%20a%20blue-collar%20industry%20they%20know%20nothing%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20that%20search%20funds%20date%20all%20the%20way%20back%20to%201984%2C%20when%20an%20HBS%20professor%20dreamed%20up%20the%20concept%20as%20a%20more%20attainable%20path%20to%20entrepreneurship%20for%20his%20students%20who%20didn't%20want%20to%20start%20a%20whole%20new%20company.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20idea%20slowly%20gained%20traction%20within%20tiny%20circles%20at%20the%20top%20business%20schools.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gsb.stanford.edu%2Ffaculty-research%2Fcase-studies%2F2024-search-fund-study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20from%20Stanford%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20from%201984%20to%202019%20investors%20had%20deployed%20a%20total%20of%20at%20least%20%241.4%20billion%20into%20search%20funds%20and%20the%20companies%20that%20so-called%20searchers%20went%20on%20to%20acquire.%20But%20it%20was%20during%20the%20pandemic%20that%20the%20movement%20really%20took%20off%2C%20fanned%20by%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20business%20school%20classes%20and%20TikTok%20influencers%20and%20podcasters%20spreading%20the%20gospel.%20In%20just%20the%20four%20years%20since%2C%20another%20%241.5%20billion%20has%20poured%20in.%20Add%20to%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20self-funded%20searchers%2C%20who%20combine%20their%20own%20savings%20with%20low-interest%20government%20loans%20to%20finance%20their%20purchases%2C%20and%20you%20get%20an%20ever-expanding%20web%20of%20young%20people%20buying%20and%20running%20small%20businesses%20all%20over%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20pandemic%20that%20changed%20so%20much%20about%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelationship%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20an%20economy%20that's%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs-major-round-managers-workers-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econstant%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20norm%2C%20with%20a%20future%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hiring-white-collar-recession-jobs-tech-new-data-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20shrink%20the%20opportunities%20of%20the%20white-collar%20class%2C%20the%20dream%20of%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20has%20never%20held%20less%20appeal.%20A%20growing%20contingent%20of%20elite%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20has%20sought%20and%20found%20an%20alternative%2C%20and%20I%20set%20out%20to%20talk%20to%20as%20many%20of%20them%20as%20I%20could%20find.%20I%20wanted%20to%20learn%20exactly%20how%20a%20person%20actually%20goes%20from%20Point%20A%20(cog%20in%20the%20corporate%20machine)%20to%20Point%20B%20(CEO%20of%20an%20extremely%20random%20and%20surprisingly%20lucrative%20business).%20That's%20how%20I%20ended%20up%20in%20Fairfax%2C%20Virginia%2C%20on%20the%20doorstep%20of%20Atlantic%20Duct%20Cleaning%2C%20the%20business%20Dan%20Schweber%20bought%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20his%20salt-and-pepper%20hair%2C%20there%20was%20a%20boyish%20enthusiasm%20to%20Schweber%2C%20as%20if%20he%20still%20couldn't%20quite%20believe%20that%20this%20%E2%80%94%20the%2030%20trucks%2C%20the%2061%20employees%2C%20the%204%2C600%20Google%20reviews%20of%20the%20company%20with%20an%20average%20five-star%20rating%20%E2%80%94%20was%20all%20his.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20the%20best%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20never%20work%20in%20a%20corporate%20job%20ever%20again.%20There's%20no%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20you%20could%20give%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Atlanta%2C%20Schweber%20was%20preternaturally%20driven%2C%20a%20little%20bundle%20of%20ambition%20dressed%20in%20his%20favorite%20truck-print%20shirts.%20At%20age%206%2C%20he%20started%20attending%20a%20Saturday%20school%20for%20gifted%20students%20at%20the%20local%20university.%20At%20age%2010%2C%20he%20wrote%20a%20newsletter%20and%20sold%20ads%20in%20it%20to%20businesses%20like%20the%20neighborhood%20handyman.%20Even%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20he%20rarely%20slept%20in%3A%20By%20the%20time%20his%20mom%20came%20in%20to%20wake%20him%20up%2C%20he%20was%20already%20at%20his%20desk.%20And%20he%20stayed%20just%20as%20determined%20as%20an%20adult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20years%20after%20Schweber%20quit%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-ai-mckinsey-bcg-deloitte-pwc-kpmg-chatbots-ai-tools-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsulting%3C%2Fa%3E%20job%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%2C%20he%20developed%20an%20instant%20crush%20on%20someone%20who%20was%20friends%20with%20his%20friends.%20They%20refused%20to%20set%20Schweber%20up%20with%20her%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20too%20reserved%20and%20she%20too%20outspoken%20to%20be%20a%20good%20match%2C%20they%20thought%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20pursued%20her%20for%20years%20until%20she%20finally%20agreed%20to%20a%20first%20date.%20The%20two%20were%20engaged%20by%20the%20time%20he%20took%20his%20search%20fund%20class%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20surprise%20her%20one%20bit%20that%20he%20was%20all%20in%20from%20day%20one%20of%20the%20class.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20most%20consistent%20thing%20about%20Dan%2C%26quot%3B%20Ally%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20100%25%20%3Cem%3Ethis%20is%20what%20I'm%20doing%2C%20and%20this%20is%20what%20I%20need%20to%20do%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20one%20year%20remaining%20in%20business%20school%2C%20he%20started%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsearch-fund-tips-risks-strategies-advice-how-to-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esearch%20fund%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20decided%20he%20wanted%20to%20buy%20a%20healthcare%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStep%201%20was%20raising%20his%20search%20fund%2C%20the%20money%20he'd%20need%20to%20go%20look%20for%20a%20business.%20Some%20people%20skip%20this%20process%20if%20they%20have%20savings%2C%20but%20you%20need%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20you%20might%20think.%20Searching%20is%20a%20full-time%20endeavor%20that%20typically%20stretches%20over%20two%20years%2C%20requiring%20the%20searcher%20to%20contact%20hundreds%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20business%20owners%2C%20court%20a%20fraction%20of%20them%2C%20and%20scrutinize%20every%20detail%20of%20their%20businesses%20to%20see%20if%20they're%20worth%20acquiring.%20The%20point%20of%20the%20search%20fund%20is%20to%20cover%20the%20searcher's%20cost%20of%20living%20during%20that%20time%2C%20as%20well%20as%20all%20the%20expenses%20of%20due%20diligence%2C%20like%20lawyers%2C%20accountants%2C%20and%20travel.%20Schweber%20made%20a%20list%20of%20about%20100%20search%20fund%20investors%20he%20could%20find%20online%20and%20cold-emailed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20he%20felt%20sheepish%20about%20it.%20Why%20would%20anyone%20give%20an%20MBA%20student%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanaged%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20most%20two%20or%20three%20direct%20reports%20money%20to%20go%20buy%20and%20run%20a%20whole%20business%3F%20But%20a%20fellow%20searcher%20reminded%20him%20that%20these%20investors%20needed%20him%20just%20as%20much%20as%20he%20needed%20them%3A%20They%20were%20looking%20for%20returns%20on%20their%20own%20money.%20Historically%2C%20searchers%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20deliver%20bewilderingly%20high%20returns%20that%20have%20few%20parallels%20among%20other%20asset%20classes%3A%20an%20average%204.5x%2C%20or%20an%20annual%20rate%20of%2035%25%20(compare%20that%20with%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20at%2010%25).%20By%20pitching%20in%20on%20this%20initial%20fund%2C%20investors%20get%20access%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20company%20the%20searcher%20goes%20on%20to%20acquire%20with%20very%20favorable%20terms.%20In%20just%20a%20few%20short%20months%2C%20Schweber%20raised%20his%20target%20%24480%2C000%2C%20which%20would%20pay%20him%20an%20annual%20salary%20of%20%24120%2C000%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222674%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Books%20on%20a%20windowsill.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6871315785e81483682ddbe5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221783%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchweber's%20office%20bookshelf%20at%20Atlantic%20Duct%20Cleaning.%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStep%202%3A%20the%20actual%20search.%20Schweber%20quit%20his%20day%20job%2C%20and%20with%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20left%20till%20graduation%2C%20he%20began%20his%20search%20on%20Monday%2C%20March%209%2C%202020.%20He%20had%20a%20whole%20plan%20to%20start%20attending%20trade%20shows%20and%20conferences%20and%20visit%20his%20old%20clients%20in%20the%20healthcare%20industry.%20Then%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20declared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-declares-coronavirus-pandemic-covid19-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECOVID-19%20a%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20road%20show%20plans%20now%20a%20bust%2C%20Schweber%20had%20to%20come%20up%20with%20another%20way%20to%20scout%20for%20businesses.%20One%20option%20was%20to%20work%20with%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebusiness%20brokers%2C%20who%20represent%20owners%20hoping%20to%20sell%20their%20companies.%20Searchers%20often%20go%20this%20route%20because%20it's%20more%20efficient.%20But%20what's%20easy%20for%20you%20to%20find%20is%20also%20easier%20for%20other%20buyers%20to%20find%20as%20well%2C%20and%20the%20competition%20ratchets%20up%20the%20price.%20Schweber%20opted%20to%20source%20his%20acquisition%20targets%20himself.%20He%20made%20a%20huge%20list%20of%20businesses%20that%20were%20in%20healthcare%20using%20information%20he%20scoured%20from%20industry%20association%20websites.%20Then%20he%20blanketed%20those%20businesses%20with%20automated%20emails%2C%20informing%20them%20that%20he%20was%20an%20interested%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20a%20good%20millennial%20professional%2C%20he%20tracked%20yearly%20and%20monthly%20KPIs%20for%20his%20outreach%20in%20a%20Google%20Sheet%20that%20he%20called%20his%20%26quot%3Bbattle%20plan.%26quot%3B%20He%20worked%20backward%20from%20one%20of%20the%20last%20steps%20of%20the%20search%3A%20getting%20a%20signed%20letter%20of%20intent%2C%20a%20nonbinding%20agreement%20that%20kicks%20off%20a%20monthslong%20due%20diligence%20process%20before%20the%20buyer%20and%20the%20seller%20ultimately%20agree%20to%20a%20sale.%20To%20get%20two%20signed%20LOIs%20a%20year%2C%20he%20estimated%2C%20he'd%20need%20to%20meet%2050%20owners%20in%20person.%20To%20get%20that%2C%20he'd%20need%20to%20have%20500%20introductory%20calls.%20That%20meant%20that%20he'd%20need%20to%20send%20initial%20emails%20to%204%2C800%20businesses%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resulting%20stream%20of%20rejection%20was%20relentless.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20lucky%2C%20people%20respond%20and%20say%20no%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20mostly%20silence.%26quot%3B%20On%20the%20rare%20occasions%20an%20owner%20agreed%20to%20an%20initial%20call%2C%20it'd%20turn%20out%20they%20weren't%20serious%20about%20selling%20their%20company%2C%20or%20the%20business%20wasn't%20quite%20what%20Schweber%20was%20looking%20for.%20(One%20time%20he%20unwittingly%20got%20on%20a%20call%20with%20the%20owner%20of%20a%20business%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20specialize%20in%20collecting%20recordings%20of%20extraterrestrials.)%20Some%20days%20he%20felt%20so%20dejected%20he%20didn't%20even%20open%20his%20laptop%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20%3Cem%3EI've%20got%20to%20get%20a%20job.%20I've%20got%20to%20give%20this%20up%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202020%2C%20he%20decided%20against%20looking%20in%20the%20healthcare%20industry%2C%20which%20seemed%20too%20mired%20in%20complexities%20around%20insurance%20reimbursements%20and%20regulations%2C%20and%20made%20a%20hard%20pivot%20to%20home%20and%20commercial%20services.%20Part%20of%20his%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20his%20belief%20that%20DIY%20was%20on%20its%20way%20out%20and%20that%20younger%20generations%20were%20willing%20to%20pay%20someone%20else%20to%20do%20the%20labor-intensive%20dirty%20work%20of%20improving%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%202021%2C%20he%20started%20discussions%20with%20his%20most%20promising%20prospect%20yet%3A%20a%20company%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Chicago%20that%20installs%20and%20maintains%20fire%20safety%20devices%20like%20extinguishers%2C%20alarms%2C%20and%20sprinklers.%20He%20loved%20it%2C%20his%20investors%20loved%20it%2C%20and%20he%20and%20the%20owner%20had%20even%20agreed%20on%20a%20preliminary%20purchase%20price.%20But%20after%20months%20of%20deliberations%2C%20the%20owner%20went%20quiet.%20When%20Schweber%20finally%20got%20ahold%20of%20him%2C%20the%20owner%20had%20bad%20news%3A%20He%20just%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20let%20go%20of%20his%20company%2C%20and%20he%20also%20didn't%20think%20Schweber%20was%20ready%20to%20be%20a%20CEO.%20It%20gutted%20him.%20It%20felt%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20breakup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%202022%20came%20around%2C%20Schweber%20was%2022%20months%20into%20his%20search%20with%20nothing%20to%20show%20for%20it.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20searchers%20never%20end%20up%20buying%20a%20business.%20But%20Schweber%20wasn't%20willing%20to%20conclude%20his%20search%20empty-handed.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20buy%20%3Cem%3Esomething%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20just%20get%20in%20the%20game%20and%20make%20this%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20Schweber%20typed%20%26quot%3BHVAC%26quot%3B%20into%20Google%20Maps%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20suburbs%20of%20Northern%20Virginia.%20Among%20the%20companies%20that%20came%20up%20was%20Atlantic%20Duct%20Cleaning.%20He%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20duct%20cleaning%20was%20at%20that%20point%2C%20but%20no%20matter%3A%20He%20put%20Atlantic%20into%20his%20CRM%20software%2C%20which%20emailed%20Atlantic's%20owner%2C%20Tom%20Keys.%20Then%20it%20emailed%20him%20again%2C%20and%20again%2C%20and%20again.%20After%2011%20emails%2C%20Schweber%20had%20no%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222783%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Schweber%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687131c3f748d8c055f5755f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20Schweber%20took%20over%2C%20he%20showed%20up%20at%207%20every%20morning%20as%20the%20technicians%20prepared%20their%20trucks.%20He%20went%20to%20duct%20cleaning%20jobs%20with%20them.%20He%20absorbed%20their%20knowledge%20and%20deferred%20to%20their%20expertise.%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnbeknownst%20to%20Schweber%2C%20Keys%20was%20used%20to%20receiving%20emails%20like%20this.%20He%20had%20started%20Atlantic%20in%201995%20as%20a%2028-year-old%20with%20several%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20heating%2C%20ventilation%2C%20and%20air%20conditioning%20industry.%20Even%20today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-dust-is-deep-cleaned-from-air-vents-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Educt%20cleaning%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20pretty%20obscure.%20But%20back%20then%2C%20virtually%20no%20one%20thought%20about%20the%20dust%2C%20bugs%2C%20pet%20hair%2C%20skin%20cells%2C%20mold%20spores%2C%20and%20all%20the%20other%20gunk%20that%20piles%20up%20inside%20a%20building's%20ventilation%20system%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20occasional%20need%20to%20clean%20it%20out.%20Keys%20had%20the%20idea%20to%20do%20it%20with%20newer%20equipment%20than%20the%20tiny%20operations%20he%20knew%20of%20that%20ran%20on%20bare-bones%20crews.%20He%20grew%20the%20company%20painstakingly%2C%20bit%20by%20bit.%20By%202021%2C%20Atlantic%20was%20bringing%20in%20%244%20million%20in%20annual%20sales%2C%20with%20impressive%20profit%20margins%20and%20a%20few%20dozen%20people%20on%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Keys'%20suitors%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-recruiting-apollo-jpmorgan-reactions-junior-bankers-recruiters-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E%20firms%20with%20deep%20pockets%20that%20were%20consolidating%20HVAC%20shops%20in%20the%20area.%20They%20offered%20Keys%20huge%20sums%20of%20money%20for%20his%20business%2C%20but%20he%20knew%20the%20PE%20playbook%3A%20They%20would%20almost%20certainly%20fire%20many%20of%20the%20employees%20he%20would%20leave%20behind.%20Other%20suitors%20were%20young%20searchers%20like%20Schweber%20who%20would%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20strip%20his%20company%20into%20pieces.%20But%20when%20he'd%20suggest%20they%20come%20out%20to%20see%20Atlantic%20in%20person%2C%20they%20didn't%20seem%20to%20want%20it%20all%20that%20much.%20%26quot%3BSo%20many%20people%20were%20like%2C%20%3Cem%3EOh%2C%20let%20me%20look%20at%20my%20calendar%20three%20weeks%20out%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Keys%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20know%20what%20their%20attraction%20was%20to%20such%20an%20unsexy%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpon%20receiving%20the%2012th%20email%20from%20Schweber%2C%20Keys%20finally%20picked%20up%20the%20phone%20and%20called%20him.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20call%2C%20Keys%20suggested%20Schweber%20come%20out%20to%20see%20the%20business.%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20can%20I%20come%20tomorrow%3F%26quot%3B%20Schweber%20asked.%20He%20told%20Ally%20he%20would%20be%20visiting%20a%20duct%20cleaning%20business.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20fuck%20is%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20have%20much%20of%20an%20answer.%20He%20spent%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20trying%20to%20familiarize%20himself%20with%20the%20art%20of%20duct%20cleaning%2C%20rooting%20through%20industry%20websites%20and%20watching%20amateur%20YouTube%20tutorials.%20The%20next%20morning%2C%20he%20drove%20three%20hours%20from%20their%20home%20in%20Philadelphia%20to%20Manassas%2C%20Virginia%2C%20where%20Atlantic%20was%20based%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20that%20day%20on%2C%20the%20two%20spoke%20every%20day.%20Keys%20came%20to%20trust%20Schweber%20as%20a%20young%20guy%20with%20integrity%2C%20someone%20who%20would%20look%20after%20the%20legacy%20of%20his%20creation.%20Schweber%20came%20to%20see%20Keys%20as%20an%20honest%20businessman%2C%20someone%20who%20wasn't%20hiding%20skeletons%20that%20would%20later%20sink%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20something%20fellow%20searchers%20warned%20him%20about.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20three-month%20due%20diligence%20process%2C%20Schweber%20furiously%20scrutinized%20Atlantic's%20business%20with%20his%20investors%20and%20bankers.%20In%20the%20end%2C%2015%20of%20his%20original%2018%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mix%20of%20wealthy%20people%20managing%20their%20own%20assets%20and%20institutional%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20in%20his%20search%20fund%20chipped%20in%2C%20and%20a%20loan%20from%20a%20private%20lender%20got%20him%20over%20the%20finish%20line.%20Schweber%20declined%20to%20disclose%20the%20purchase%20price.%20(The%20median%20price%20for%20companies%20bought%20by%20investor-backed%20searchers%20in%202022%20and%202023%20was%20%2414.4%20million.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2031%2C%202022%2C%20Schweber%20and%20Keys%20signed%20the%20paperwork%20to%20complete%20the%20transaction.%20After%2C%20Schweber%20got%20into%20his%20car%20and%20cried.%20In%20the%20three%20years%20since%20he%20first%20decided%20in%20his%20Columbia%20class%20to%20buy%20a%20small%20business%2C%20he%20had%20faced%20relentless%20doubt%20from%20skeptical%20friends%2C%20confused%20family%20members%2C%20and%20tough%20investors%20who%20were%20trying%20to%20discern%20whether%20he%20had%20what%20it%20takes%3B%20even%20he%20admitted%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Brelatively%20crazy%26quot%3B%20career%20choice.%20But%20after%203%2C592%20initial%20emails%2C%20375%20introductory%20calls%2C%2030%20introductory%20in-person%20meetings%20with%20owners%2C%20and%20six%20signed%20letters%20of%20intent%2C%20he%20was%20now%20the%20proud%20owner%20of%20what%20was%20by%20all%20accounts%20a%20trusted%20local%20business.%20That%20night%2C%20he%20and%20Ally%20opened%20a%20bottle%20of%20champagne%20to%20celebrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20morning%2C%20a%20nervous%20Schweber%20joined%20Keys%2C%20who%20gathered%20the%20staff%20in%20the%20office%20to%20break%20the%20big%20news%3A%20Schweber%20was%20the%20new%20owner%20of%20Atlantic.%20No%20one%20even%20knew%20the%20company%20was%20up%20for%20sale%2C%20aside%20from%20the%20two%20managers%20Keys%20had%20informed%20the%20day%20before.%20%3Cem%3EWhat%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20staff%20erupted.%20%3Cem%3EWhy%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3ESchweber%20knew%20what%20it%20looked%20like%3A%20Here%20he%20was%2C%20a%2032-year-old%2C%20telling%20this%20staff%20of%2040%20or%20so%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20decades%20older%20than%20him%2C%20that%20he%20was%20suddenly%20their%20new%20boss.%20He%20was%20walking%20a%20tightrope%20that%20every%20searcher%20does%20on%20day%20one%20as%20CEO%3A%20projecting%20an%20air%20of%20both%20authority%20and%20humility%20as%20a%20first-time%20boss-in-chief.%20%26quot%3BI%20bought%20this%20company%20because%20I%20like%20what%20you%20guys%20are%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20his%20new%20staff.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20the%20best%20in%20our%20market%20at%20what%20we%20do%2C%20and%20I%20just%20want%20to%20do%20more.%20So%20as%20long%20as%20you%20want%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20grow%2C%20you'll%20always%20have%20a%20spot%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchweber's%20long%2C%20tortuous%20search%20for%20a%20business%20was%20over.%20Now%20came%20the%20hard%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20goes%20into%20a%20search%20thinking%20they'll%20tank%20the%20company%20they%20buy.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20these%20people%2C%20they've%20had%20tremendous%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Matthew%20Zucker%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20ETA%20Equity%2C%20who's%20been%20investing%20in%20search%20funds%20since%202008.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20always%20been%20top%20quartile%20of%20everything%2C%20so%20they%20think%20they're%20going%20to%20get%20top%20quartile%20results.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20among%20these%20extreme%20overachievers%2C%20not%20every%20deal%20goes%20on%20to%20mint%20money.%20Of%20all%20the%20searchers%20who%20buy%20a%20company%2C%2031%25%20end%20up%20losing%20money%20for%20their%20investors.%20Usually%20those%20businesses%20limp%20along%3B%20occasionally%2C%20they%20implode%20spectacularly%20%E2%80%94%20straight%20into%20bankruptcy.%20A%20recession%20hits.%20A%20flaw%20missed%20in%20due%20diligence%20brings%20the%20business%20to%20a%20screeching%20halt.%20Or%20the%20CEO%20just%20can't%20cut%20it%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20case%2C%20if%20the%20board%20catches%20on%20quickly%20enough%2C%20they'll%20fire%20the%20searcher%20and%20bring%20in%20someone%20else.%20These%20are%20the%20nightmare%20scenarios%20that%20start%20to%20haunt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-are-americas-entreprenuers-women-immigrants-living-south-side-hustle-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20entrepreneurs%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20they%20take%20over%20the%20companies%20they've%20just%20purchased.%20Having%20taken%20on%20millions%20in%20investor%20capital%20and%20debt%2C%20suddenly%20responsible%20for%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20dozens%20of%20employees%2C%20and%20facing%20an%20impossibly%20steep%20learning%20curve%2C%20many%20struggle%20to%20adjust%20to%20the%20crushing%20pressures%20of%20being%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20guy%20who%20bought%20an%20electrical%20contractor%20in%20Grand%20Rapids%2C%20Michigan%2C%20told%20me%20he%20spiraled%20into%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrisis%20of%20self-doubt%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20early%20months.%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20to%20panic.%20%3Cem%3EDo%20I%20have%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20run%20this%20business%3F%20Are%20people%20going%20to%20see%20through%20me%3F%20Are%20customers%20going%20to%20think%20I'm%20an%20idiot%20because%20I%20don't%20understand%20electrical%20theory%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20Another%20guy%20who%20bought%20a%20small%20transportation%20software%20company%20in%20New%20York%20City%20told%20me%20that%2C%20for%20the%20first%20year%2C%20he%20often%20cried%20in%20the%20morning%20in%20his%20car%20before%20walking%20into%20the%20office.%20A%20third%20guy%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20pretty%20much%20all%20guys%3B%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20count%2C%20only%2017%25%20of%20new%20searchers%20were%20women%2C%20an%20improvement%20from%20the%200%25%20for%20much%20of%20the%202000s%20%E2%80%94%20watched%20his%20newly%20purchased%20car%20wash's%20revenue%20fall%20off%20a%20cliff%20during%20a%20historically%20rainy%20stretch.%20He%20had%20underestimated%20just%20how%20volatile%20the%20car%20washing%20business%20can%20be.%20It%20got%20so%20bad%20that%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20to%20float%20a%20couple%20of%20checks%20to%20the%20company%20just%20so%20it%20could%20make%20payroll.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20for%20the%20first%20six%20months%2C%20I%20said%2C%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20the%20hell%20have%20I%20done%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20this%20desk%20job.%20I%20had%20all%20this%20salary%20coming%20in.%20Did%20I%20just%20blow%20up%20everything%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222783%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Schweber%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68713286f748d8c055f57598%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchweber's%20goal%20is%20for%20Atlantic%20to%20make%20%2425%20million%20a%20year%20by%202028.%20By%20then%2C%20he%20wants%20it%20to%20be%20the%20largest%20air%20duct%20cleaning%20company%20on%20the%20East%20Coast%2C%20maybe%20even%20the%20country.%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Schweber%20remembers%20from%20those%20early%20months%20is%20just%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20tasks%20he%20had%20to%20tick%20through.%20He%20spent%20the%20first%20few%20weeks%20resetting%20passwords%2C%20getting%20access%20to%20the%20business'%20bank%20accounts%2C%20and%20figuring%20out%20which%20employees%20had%20company%20credit%20cards.%20Then%20he%20focused%20on%20getting%20to%20know%20his%20staff.%20He%20showed%20up%20at%207%20every%20morning%20as%20the%20technicians%20prepared%20their%20trucks%20for%20their%20assignments%20of%20the%20day.%20He%20went%20to%20duct%20cleaning%20jobs%20with%20them.%20He%20took%20them%20out%20to%20lunch.%20He%20absorbed%20their%20knowledge%2C%20solicited%20their%20feedback%2C%20and%20deferred%20to%20their%20expertise.%20He%20occasionally%20floated%20some%20new%20ideas%20%E2%80%94%20could%20they%20overbook%20jobs%20the%20way%20airlines%20oversell%20seats%2C%20because%20some%20customers%20cancel%20last-minute%3F%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20backed%20down%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20faced%20a%20little%20resistance.%20He%20didn't%