20so%20far%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20impatience%2C%20it's%20clear%20he%20loves%20pretty%20much%20every%20aspect%20of%20the%20job.%20Everything%20about%20it%20is%20different%20from%20the%20consulting%20job%20he%20landed%20out%20of%20college.%20Back%20then%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20building%20spreadsheets%20and%20PowerPoints%20for%20my%20boss%2C%20who%20built%20it%20for%20their%20boss.%26quot%3B%20It%20would%20take%2012%20to%2015%20years%20just%20to%20get%20high%20enough%20on%20the%20totem%20pole%20to%20make%20any%20decision%20of%20consequence%20%E2%80%94%20and%20from%20what%20he%20could%20tell%20from%20his%20lowly%20vantage%20point%2C%20even%20that%20job%20as%20a%20managing%20director%20didn't%20seem%20all%20that%20great.%20At%20any%20rate%2C%20he%20wasn't%20willing%20to%20sit%20around%20for%20that%20long%20to%20find%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20Atlantic%2C%20he%20has%20the%20power%20to%20make%20all%20the%20decisions.%20That%20includes%20the%20big%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20like%20offering%20health%20insurance%20to%20his%20employees%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20and%20experimenting%20with%20a%20new%20line%20of%20business%20cleaning%20trash%20chutes.%20And%20it%20includes%20the%20small%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20like%20taking%20his%20son%20to%20swim%20lessons%20every%20Wednesday%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20wearing%20shorts%20to%20the%20office%20when%20it%20gets%20hot%20in%20the%20summer.%20They're%20liberties%20he's%20still%20getting%20used%20to.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20control%20every%20customer%20that%20we%20have%20or%20every%20employee%20that%20works%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20can%20effect%20change.%20If%20this%20doesn't%20work%20out%2C%20I%20probably%20have%20no%20one%20to%20blame%20except%20myself.%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20total%20control%20over%20my%20destiny.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheesy%20as%20it%20sounds%2C%20that's%20the%20sentiment%20I've%20heard%20most%20from%20the%20searchers%20I've%20spoken%20with%20in%20these%20past%20few%20months.%20They%20say%20the%20salary%20is%20decent%20(the%20average%20search%20CEO%20makes%20between%20%24200%2C000%20and%20%24300%2C000%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20most%20people%20but%20often%20less%20than%20their%20MBA%20peers%20in%20finance%2C%20consulting%2C%20and%20Big%20Tech).%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-performance-evaluations-management-reviews-promotions-raises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20so-so%20%E2%80%94%20you%20control%20your%20schedule%2C%20but%20you're%20never%20truly%20unplugged.%20The%20financial%20windfall%20down%20the%20road%20is%20potentially%20life-changing.%20But%20what%20matters%20most%20to%20them%20is%20the%20agency%20to%20make%20their%20own%20decisions%2C%20and%20to%20see%20those%20decisions%20move%20the%20needle.%20They're%20not%20changing%20the%20world%2C%20but%20they%20are%20making%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20handful%20of%20employees%20they%20have%20and%20the%20customers%20they%20serve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20you're%20always%20going%20to%20get%20that%20layer%20where%20it's%20just%20not%20your%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20transportation%20guy%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BMy%20managers%20really%20drove%20the%20business%2C%20and%20all%20I%20did%20was%20help%20them.%20I%20can't%20go%20back%20to%20an%20environment%20where%20I'm%20somewhere%20in%20the%20middle.%26quot%3B%20That's%20why%2C%20after%20selling%20his%20company%20for%20three%20times%20its%20original%20value%2C%20he%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20getting%20another%20job.%20Recently%2C%20he%20raised%20his%20next%20search%20fund%20to%20do%20it%20all%20over%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222783%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Schweber%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68713a193d5881a51c1d2e95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20his%20corporate%20career%2C%20says%20Schweber%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20building%20spreadsheets%20and%20PowerPoints%20for%20my%20boss%2C%20who%20built%20it%20for%20their%20boss.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20Atlantic%2C%20he%20has%20the%20power%20to%20make%20all%20the%20decisions.%3Cp%3ELexey%20Swall%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20world%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-recession-hiring-slump-jobs-tech-industry-applications-rejection-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20gets%20ever%20more%20depressing%20by%20the%20day%2C%20an%20entire%20generation%20of%20smart%2C%20ambitious%20young%20Americans%20is%20out%20there%20searching%20for%20a%20new%20dream%20to%20aspire%20to%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20replaces%20the%20one%20their%20parents%20and%20grandparents%20had%20of%20becoming%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20a%20large%20corporation%20one%20day.%20Ever%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I've%20been%20asking%3A%20What%20will%20that%20new%20dream%20be%3F%20For%20some%2C%20it's%20been%20work-life%20balance.%20For%20others%2C%20it's%20been%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-earn-money-side-hustles-creative-passive-income-ideas-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassive-income%20side%20hustle%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretiring%20early%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20becoming%20a%20digital%20nomad.%20For%20Schweber%2C%20it's%20been%20buying%20and%20running%20a%20duct%20cleaning%20business%20in%20the%20Virginia%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchweber%20insists%20that%20anyone%20could%20do%20it.%20I'm%20skeptical.%20To%20make%20it%20work%2C%20it%20takes%20extraordin